credit_line: Gift of Eleanor and Sarah Hewitt
title: Table cover
medium:
Medium: linen
Technique: crochet, bobbin lace
description: Linen center; lace border with the initials EGH, MHY, SCH, and AMY, and Italian place names worked in crocheted lace; edging of bobbin lace. This lace was crocheted and the tablecloth made by Miss Eleanor Hewitt after an Italian trip made by herself and her sisters with Mrs. A. Murray Young. The initials of the travellers are worked in the lace.
name: Table cover
